250 g Ground Turkey
¾ cup Basmati Rice
160 g Sweet Bell Pepper
56 g Onion, chopped
1 unit(s) Green Onion
½ cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
2 tbsp Ketchup
2 tbsp Mexican Seasoning
1 tbsp Vegetable Stock Powder
1 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves

Before starting, add 1 1/4 cups (2 1/2 cups) water to a medium pot. Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.Wash and dry all produce. Once water is boiling, add rice, stock powder and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Stir to combine.Reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 12-14 min. Remove the pot from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, core, then cut pepper into 1/2-inch pieces.﻿Peel, then mince or grate garlic.Finely chop green onion.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.When hot, add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then onions and peppers. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are tender-crisp, 3-4 min. Season with salt and pepper.Transfer veggies to a plate, cover to keep warm.

Add 1/2 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then turkey. Cook, breaking up meat into smaller pieces, until no pink remains, 4-5 min.** Season with salt and pepper.

Reduce heat to medium.Add Mexican Seasoning, garlic, ketchup and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water to the pan with turkey. Cook, stirring often, until fragrant, 1 min.When rice is done, add veggies and rice to the pan. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.Reduce heat to low, then sprinkle cheese over top. Cover and cook until cheese melts, 2-3 min.

Divide turkey skillet rice between plates.Sprinkle green onions over top.